	<element name="Iron Protector" type="Archetype Feature" source="The Greasemonkey's Handbook" id="ID_TGMHB_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_DRUID_STEEL_IRON_PROTECTOR">
		<description>
			<p>When you reach 10th level, your companion becomes resistant to nonmagical bludgeoning, piercing and slashing damage from ranged weapon attacks. It extends this feature to you while you remain within 10 feet of it.</p>
		</description>
		<sheet>
			<description>Your companion becomes resistant to nonmagical bludgeoning, piercing and slashing damage from ranged weapon attacks. It extends this feature to you while you remain within 10 feet of it.</description>
		</sheet>
	</element>
	<element name="Improved Steel Bond" type="Archetype Feature" source="The Greasemonkey's Handbook" id="ID_TGMHB_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_DRUID_STEEL_IMPROVED_STEEL_BOND">
		<description>
			<p>At 14th level, your companion gains the Shield Guardian’s <i>Shield</i> and <i>Spell Storing</i> features. You can use both features only once per long rest (see page 271 of the Monster Manual for more details).</p>
			<p class="indent">Your companion always treats you as its master, though you require no amulet in order for you or it to perform either ability. If your companion is knocked unconcious, it immediately loses its stored spell.</p>
			<p class="indent"><b><i>Shield (1 Reaction).</i></b> When a creature makes an attack against you, the Steel Companion grants a +2 bonus to your AC if the companion is within 5 feet of you.</p>
			<p class="indent"><b><i>Spell Storing (Trait).</i></b> You can cause your Steel Companion to store one spell of 4th level or lower. To do so, you must cast the spell on the companion. The spell has no effect but is stored within the companion. When commanded to do so by you or when a situation arises that was predefined by you, the companion casts the stored spell with any parameters set by you, requiring no components. When the spell is cast or a new spell is stored, any previously stored spell is lost.</p>
		</description>
		<sheet>
			<description>Your companion gains the Shield Guardian’s <i>Shield</i> and <i>Spell Storing</i> features (treating you as the wearer of the amulet).</description>
		</sheet>
	</element>
	
	
	
